<br>
Hot key set up that I suggest is something like this. Let's say 1st MT is Holy, 2nd MT is Evolon, and Holy went down after his defensive disc wears off..<br>
<br>
/assist Evolon<br>
/attack off<br>
/pause 50 &lt;- 5 secs pause, maybe longer if needed.<br>
/attack <br>
<br>
During that pause, Nolove will hit her defensive disc and keeps on attacking while taunting. That way, she builds up aggro.<br>
<br>
Only use this hotkey for main mobs like Velks, Vindi, Tormax etc. Do not use this hotkey set up with regular mutli mobs when we are doing a dungeon crawl like DN, Chardok, Hole etc.<br>
<br>
I also agree with what Bola covered above, that the MTs have their hotley set up as such. So that the next MT gets ready to move in. <p><center><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~malousek/_uimages/JaraanSig.jpg>
